tries section (`EntriesTable` over `PeekRoundEntryRow`):\n1761\t  - Columns: created, user, wallet, amount lamports (right-aligned), side,\n1762\t    winner, payout lamports (right-aligned), settled. The `user` cell\n1763\t    becomes a `Link` to `/users/[userId]` (FR-6 drill-down) showing\n1764\t    `username` when `player_profiles` had a row, falling back to a\n1765\t    truncated user id with the full id in `title=`.\n1766\t  - `isWinner` renders as `yes`/`no`/`—` so an operator can scan winners\n1767\t    quickly. Lamport zeros stay as `\"0\"` (measured zero), but null\n1768\t    settledAt / null side render `—` to avoid mistaking sparse data for a\n1769\t    measured outcome.\n1770\t  - Sparse state explains the absence operationally — \"No entries recorded\n1771\t    for this round\" + \"the `game_entries` table has no rows joined to this\n1772\t    round PDA. This is normal for rounds that were created but never\n1773\t    joined.\" — matching the FR-3 empty-state convention used elsewhere in\n1774\t    `peek`.\n1775\t- Transactions section (`TransactionsTable` over\n1776\t  `PeekRoundTransactionRow`):\n1777\t  - Columns: created, type (StatusChip), user (Link or `—`), wallet,\n1778\t    amount lamports (right-aligned), tx signature (mono + truncated +\n1779\t    `title=`). User column is null when the chain row has no resolved\n1780\t    `user_id` so the table doesn't fabricate a user link.\n1781\t  - Sparse state references the FR-8 stuck-state filter on\n1782\t    `/games/[game]` (\"settled rounds without transaction rows are an\n1783\t    attention state surfaced by the stuck-state filters\") so an operator\n1784\t    arriving from a stuck-state filter has a clear hint about what they're\n1785\t    looking at.\n1786\t- Role gating: the route falls under the default `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES`\n1787\t  (business + admin) — no explicit prefix rule needed because the round\n1788\t  detail isn't admin-only. `/audit` remains the only admin-gated prefix in\n1789