ns\n1823\t    both empty → empty arrays), refunded (`phase = 'expired'` + a refund\n1824\t    transaction), stuck (`phase = 'settling'`, `settleAttempts = '12'`\n1825\t    string coercion, no winner), `null` returned when the round is not\n1826\t    found (and no follow-up entries/transactions queries fire), the\n1827\t    defense-in-depth `PEEK_ROUNDS_GAME_IDS` filter (a bogus `crash` row\n1828\t    cannot leak), `isWinner = null` staying null (not coerced to false),\n1829\t    transactions with null `user_id` keeping `userId` null (no fabricated\n1830\t    link), and load-error propagation from either parallel query.\n1831\t  - Close Call branch covers: full populated round (settled / green) with\n1832\t    the CC-specific column shape (`outcome`, `roundId`, `openPriceExpo`,\n1833\t    pools, fee), the SQL contract that joins transactions through\n1834\t    `round_id` (not `match_id`) and hard-codes `t.game = 'closecall'`,\n1835\t    sparse (open + pending with empty pools), refunded (`phase =\n1836\t    'refunded'` + `outcome = 'refund'` + a refund transaction), stuck\n1837\t    (open round with empty entries + transactions still drillable), null\n1838\t    when not found, the Pyth `openPriceExpo` integer coercion from a\n1839\t    postgres string, and load-error propagation.\n1840\t- New `peek/src/components/__tests__/round-detail-view.test.tsx`\n1841\t  (18 tests):\n1842\t  - FlipYou (full): every spec-required summary field renders; phase\n1843\t    `StatusChip`s carry the right tone; u64 lamport > MAX_SAFE_INTEGER\n1844\t    formats with thousands separators (preserves underlying digits);\n1845\t    entries table user-link drills to `/users/[userId]` (FR-6); singular\n1846\t    \"1 participant\" / \"1 on-chain SOL movement\" hint pluralises correctly.\n1847\t  - FlipYou (sparse): both empty states render; pluralised count hints\n1848\t    swap to \"0 participants\" / \"0 on-chain SOL movements\".\n1849\t  - FlipYou (em-dashes): null `targetSlot`/`settleTx`/`r